<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Sharding on Finisky Garden</title><link>https://finisky.github.io/en/tags/sharding/</link><description>Recent content in Sharding on Finisky Garden</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 22 Oct 2021 20:05:26 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://finisky.github.io/en/tags/sharding/rss.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>How to Get the MongoDB Chunk Size</title><link>https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-get-chunk-size/</link><pubDate>Fri, 22 Oct 2021 20:05:26 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-get-chunk-size/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Recently we found the traffic is not balanced across the MongoDB cluster shards. After investigation, the root cause is that data on each shard is not evenly distributed (
&lt;a href="https://www.mongodb.com/blog/post/sharding-pitfalls-part-iii-chunk-balancing-and" title="Chunk balancing != data balancing != traffic balancing" rel="noopener external nofollow noreferrer" target="_blank" class=" exturl"&gt;
 Chunk balancing != data balancing != traffic balancing
 
 &lt;i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 
&lt;/a&gt;). The data distribution looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Shard&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Data Size&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;mongo-0&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;10.55 GB&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;mongo-1&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;25.76 GB&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;mongo-2&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;10.04 GB&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why the data size of &lt;code&gt;mongo-1&lt;/code&gt; is significantly large than others while the chunk number among 3 shards is almost the same? Then we need to analysis the chunk size distribution across these shards.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>MongoDB Chunk Migration Failed Solution: Unable to acquire X lock</title><link>https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-chunk-migration-failed/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 12:00:01 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-chunk-migration-failed/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;After adding new shards to our production MongoDB cluster (v4.4.6-ent with 5 shards, 3 replicas for each shard), we found that the balancer is not working. &lt;code&gt;sh.status()&lt;/code&gt; displays many chunk migration errors:&lt;/p&gt;

