&lt;!-- more --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Obviously, the chunks is unbalanced accross shards (327 vs 208). Since the balancer is enabled, we try to debug the issue through &lt;code&gt;mongodb.log&lt;/code&gt; on the config server. There are many migration failed logs (sensitive infomation masked):&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Don't Use Load Balancer In front of Mongos</title><link>https://finisky.github.io/en/dont-use-load-balancer-in-front-of-mongos/</link><pubDate>Wed, 13 Jan 2021 23:38:36 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://finisky.github.io/en/dont-use-load-balancer-in-front-of-mongos/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;When I execute MongoDB transactions in parallel, I encounter lots of &lt;code&gt;MongoCommandException&lt;/code&gt;: code 251, codename &lt;code&gt;NoSuchTransaction&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;blockquote&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;Command find failed: cannot continue txnId 4 for session 38604515-2584-45a5-a17a-5eb5d34ea6c4 - = with txnId 5.
Command find failed: cannot continue txnId 4 for session 38604515-2584-45a5-a17a-5eb5d34ea6c4 - = with txnId 6.
Command insert failed: cannot continue txnId 31 for session 3ed7ea61-eae1-440f-8d95-b6e066b35b69 - = with txnId 34.&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;!-- more --&gt;
&lt;h1 id="problem-analysis"&gt;Problem Analysis
&lt;a class="header-anchor" href="#problem-analysis"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;I performed some tests to pinpoint the issue:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy MongoDB Sharded Cluster by Ops Manager</title><link>https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-om-create-sharded-cluster/</link><pubDate>Sat, 26 Dec 2020 22:18:10 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-om-create-sharded-cluster/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;MongoDB sharded cluster is the most complicated architecture. The deployment of sharded cluster in Kubernetes is relatively hard. We will go through the deployment process by MongoDB Ops Manager in this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before start, please go through the 
&lt;a href="https://finisky.github.io/en/mongodb-om-create-user-db/" title="Create a UserDB ReplicaSet" &gt;
 Create a UserDB ReplicaSet
 
&lt;/a&gt; first.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A MongoDB 
&lt;a href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/glossary/#term-sharded-cluster" title="sharded cluster" rel="noopener external nofollow noreferrer" target="_blank" class=" exturl"&gt;
 sharded cluster
 
 &lt;i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 
&lt;/a&gt; consists of the following components:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/core/sharded-cluster-shards/" title="shard" rel="noopener external nofollow noreferrer" target="_blank" class=" exturl"&gt;
 shard
 
 &lt;i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 
&lt;/a&gt;: Each shard contains a subset of the sharded data. Each shard can be deployed as a 
&lt;a href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/glossary/#term-replica-set" title="replica set" rel="noopener external nofollow noreferrer" target="_blank" class=" exturl"&gt;
 replica set
 
 &lt;i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 
&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/core/sharded-cluster-query-router/" title="mongos" rel="noopener external nofollow noreferrer" target="_blank" class=" exturl"&gt;
 mongos
 
 &lt;i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 
&lt;/a&gt;: The &lt;code&gt;mongos&lt;/code&gt; acts as a query router, providing an interface between client applications and the sharded cluster.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/core/sharded-cluster-config-servers/" title="config servers" rel="noopener external nofollow noreferrer" target="_blank" class=" exturl"&gt;
 config servers
 
 &lt;i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 
&lt;/a&gt;: Config servers store metadata and configuration settings for the cluster.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this post, we are going to create a sharded cluster with 2 shards (3 instances replica set), 2 mongos and 3 config servers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>